title: Excess winter deaths, United Kingdom, 2004-07
name: Excess winter deaths, United Kingdom, 2004-07
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on 	excess winter deaths. England, in common with other European countries, experiences higher levels of mortality in the winter than in the summer. There is some evidence to suggest that excess winter mortality (EWM) is preventable. Mortality in winter increases more in England compared to other European countries with colder climates, suggesting that it is more than just lower temperatures responsible for the excess mortality in winter.
